4 Sec. 1. 16 V.S.A. § 1388 is amended to read:
5 § 1388. STOCK SUPPLY AND EMERGENCY ADMINISTRATION OF
6 EPINEPHRINE AUTO-INJECTORS
7 (a) As used in this section:
8 (1) “Designated personnel” means a school employee, agent, or
9 volunteer who has completed training required by State Board policy and who
10 has been authorized by the school administrator or delegated by the school
11 nurse to provide and administer epinephrine auto-injectors under in accordance
12 with a provider’s standing order or protocol pursuant to this section and who
13 has completed the training required by State Board policy.
14 (2) “Epinephrine auto-injector” means a U.S. Food and Drug
15 Administration-approved single-use device that delivers a epinephrine delivery
16 system containing a premeasured single dose of epinephrine.
17 (3) “Health care professional” means a physician licensed pursuant to 26
18 V.S.A. chapter 23 or 33, an advanced practice registered nurse licensed to
19 prescribe drugs and medical devices pursuant to 26 V.S.A. chapter 28, or a
20 physician assistant licensed to prescribe drugs and medical devices pursuant to
21 26 V.S.A. chapter 31.
